HEADWORD: Euhemerism
<hw>Eu*hem"er*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Euhemerus</ets>, Gr. <?/ a philosopher, about 300 <?/.]</ety>
<def>The theory, held by <persfn>Euhemerus</persfn>, that the gods of
mythology were but deified mortals, and their deeds only the
amplification in imagination of human acts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

